# Find Your Knowns

Use this rule when a request is vague, unfamiliar, design-heavy, reference-based,
high-risk, long-running, or likely to hide product, API, data, security, or
operational constraints.

Load and follow:

```text
skills/find-your-knowns/SKILL.md
```

Important boundaries:

- Use Find Your Knowns to discover missing context before implementation.
- Do not use it as ordinary code review, bug review, security review, or PR
  defect finding.
- Inspect the actual repo or product surface before ranking risks.
- Ask one high-impact question at a time only when the answer would change the
  implementation.
- Produce a concrete artifact: risk table, direction set, reference map,
  implementation note, buy-in doc, or change quiz.

Useful prompts:

```text
Use Find Your Knowns before planning this feature.
```

```text
Run a blindspot pass on this module before implementation.
```

```text
Show design directions before wiring the real UI.
```
